volunteer_experiences:
[{'date': {'start': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}, 'end': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}}, 'role': 'Public Affairs Volunteer', 'company': {'id': None, 'name': 'European Citizen Initiative - Ending the aviation fuel tax exemption in Europe', 'logo': None, 'url': None}, 'cause': 'ENVIRONMENT', 'description': 'I set up the signature website with the IT support of the European Commission (https://eci.ec.europa.eu/008/public/#/initiative). In addition, I was part of the team reaching out to politics to persuade them to take the matter of aviation fuel tax exemption in Europe up the agenda. I received positive feedback from the secretariat of President Macron, members of European Parliament and local party leaders in Belgium. In this role, I also personally liaised with Green Peace Netherlands and Transport&Environment to foster synergy between our common goal.

In addition, I had two interviews in a Belgian newspaper to raise awareness about the impact of aviation on the environment and how a tax on kerosene would function.
